br />\n<br />\nHackers believed to be linked to the Chinese government have broken into the systems of more than a dozen global telecommunications carriers and stolen huge amounts of data over a period going back at least seven years, according to a new report today from security researchers at Cybereason.<br />\n<br />\nThe hackers also used tools linked to other attacks attributed to Beijing by the United States and its Western allies, said Lior Div, chief executive of Cybereason. &ldquo;For this level of sophistication it&rsquo;s not a criminal group. It is a government that has capabilities that can do this kind of attack,&rdquo; he told Reuters. <br />\n<br />\nThe hacking campaign, dubbed Operation Soft Cell, targeted &ldquo;call detail records&rdquo; that contained metadata on every call made on a targeted network, including times, dates and the location of the device. <br />\n<br />\nIn addition, the same group attempted to steal all data stored by their targets, including usernames and password in the organization, billing data, email servers and other related information.<br />\n<br />\nThe tools used by hackers were those commonly associated with the APT10 group, a hacking group that works on behalf of the Chinese Ministry of State Security&rsquo;s Tianjin State Security Bureau. Members of the group were indicted by the U.S. Department of Justice in December 2018.<br />\n<br />\nGiving credence to the idea that it was a state-sponsored campaign, the researchers noted that &ldquo;the threat actor mainly sought to obtain CDR data (call logs, cell tower locations, etc.) belonging to specific individuals from various countries. This type of targeted cyber espionage is usually the work of nation-state threat actors.<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20191215181157/https://siliconangle.com/2019/06/25/data-stolen-global-telcos-suspected-chinese-hacking-campaign/\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fweb.archive.org%2Fweb%2F20191215181157%2Fhttps%3A%2F%2Fsiliconangle.com%2F2019%2F06%2F25%2Fdata-stolen-global-telcos-suspected-chinese-hacking-campaign%2F&d=CEXeqV9R6719hdRRqmVjOubr9%2BGymSeLOXabm6KdyvY%3D&h=15ce349b\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://web.archive.org/web/20191215181157/https://siliconangle.com/2019/06/25/data-stolen-global-telcos-suspected-chinese-hacking-campaign/</a><br />\n<br />\n<span style=\"color: pink;\"><span style=\"font-size: xx-large;\">想睇吓點可以阻到支那 hack 你？即刻撳入嚟睇</span></span><br />\n<br />\n唔想再有手足被黑警自殺？用呢4個apps! (啱所有人用，尤其前線手足)<br />\n- 分享自 LIHKG 討論區<br />\n<a href=\"https://lihkg.com/thread/1864933/page/7?ref=sharer&amp;post=172\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://lihkg.com/thread/1864933/page/7?ref=sharer&amp;post=172</a><br />\n<br />\n請大家幫手正評，幫推，避免沉底, P牌推唔郁"},{"pid":"45ffdcb0190d0a406ba5f948a61a739f6bdac8df","tid":1870550,"uid":28163,"like":7,"dislike":2,"score":5,"quote":{"pid":"d04c12cb3aca6faad9f253dd2ffc028cf0f8458d","tid":1870550,"uid":63491,"like":7,"dislike":2,"score":5,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-02-09T04:45:10.000Z","msg":"台灣執香港死雞"},"citedBy":3,"replyTime":"2020-02-09T05:09:17.000Z","msg":"人地自己爭取<br />\n佢地總統抗共果一刻<br />\n放棄中國市場<br />\n轉向美國<br />\n<br />\n我地擁抱大灣區<br />\n放棄外國<br />\n完全自己攞嚟"},{"pid":"39ba4260ef82693c540639d7822f65bdd6a67d82","tid":1870550,"uid":299694,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-02-09T05:11:19.000Z","msg":"支那又贏"},{"pid":"f3510238217238a89682b543c82af41d7d137190","tid":1870550,"uid":249885,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-02-09T05:13:21.000Z","msg":"點解要駁香港 唔可以駁東京 首爾"},{"pid":"98e7929c8c42b9e4afe018105300dc5d3c9fc401","tid":1870550,"uid":37820,"like":0,"dislike":1,"score":-1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-02-09T05:19:18.000Z","msg":"香港人都讚成鋪去台灣啦<br />\n賓就算鳩數啦<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/dead.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"ef5d9d4a58e1c0ba51b6578621c9c165a2adb07d","tid":1870550,"uid":344033,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-02-09T0